DURBAN - Mamelodi Sundowns are through to the final of the Telkom Knockout. The Brazilians beat Golden Arrows 2-1 in Durban. They hit the target through Gaston Sirino and Hlompho Kekana in the first half. READ: Arrows storm to victory over Sundowns Arrows pulled one back late in the second half. Sirino was sent off shortly after, but Steve Komphela's side could not capitalize on that advantage as Sundowns reached the final with a 2-1 win.